-- Santander says will increase U.S. business equity by up to $2 bln
-- 
-- Thu Jan 23, 2014 03:17AM EST
-- None



MADRID, Jan 23 (Reuters) - Spain's Santander <SAN.MC> said on Thursday that it intended to increase the equity of Santander Holdings USA - which houses its U.S. banking and consumer finance businesses - by up to $2 billion.

The bank, which did not specify how this capital would be raised or transferred, said it would increase the equity to support its growth plans in the United States.